dcterms:creator: B. Baker

dcterms:description: NAS-Bench-101 is the first public architecture dataset for neural architecture search (NAS) research, containing a table that maps 423k unique convolutional architectures to their training and evaluation metrics, allowing for rapid evaluation of diverse models.
dcterms:title: NAS-Bench-101

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class, commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Klein
F. Hutter
dcterms:description: NAS-Bench-Mini is a smaller subset of NAS-Bench-101 containing all cells within the search space that utilize 6 or fewer vertices, allowing for faster experimentation and analysis.
dcterms:title: NAS-Bench-Mini
